	(410,1,'2015-09-15 12:35:14','2015-09-15 12:35:14','<!--:de--><p>Als ich von ASUS, das erste, was in den Sinn kommt denken, sind die PC-Komponenten wie Mainboards, Grafikprozessoren und dergleichen. Ich denke auch an ihre Desktop-und Laptop-Computern. Ein Teil davon ist wahrscheinlich auf meiner langjährigen Interesse an PCs und PC-Gaming, aber auch so, ist die Idee des ASUS als Smartphone-Unternehmen ein, dass ich nicht so oft denken. Allerdings ASUS bietet seit Smartphones seit den Tagen von Windows Mobile, und sie haben in der Android Tablet-Raum mit ihren Transformator Tabletten und beide Generationen des Nexus 7. Mit Smartphone + Tablet-Hybriden wie der ASUS PadFone war ein sehr wichtiger Spieler, es war scheinbar unvermeidlich, dass ASUS wäre ein Konkurrent in der Welt der diskreten Android-Smartphones zu werden.</p>\n<p>Während ASUS den Fortschritt in der Region Asien-Pazifik, haben sie nicht so viel Fortschritt in der nordamerikanischen Märkten, wie ich vermute, dass sie gehofft hatte. Das bringt uns zu heute mit der ZenFone 2. Nachdem zunächst los Verkauf in ASUS Heimatland von Taiwan am 8. März, und in jüngerer Zeit in Japan und Indien hat die ZenFone 2 jetzt seinen Weg bis zu den Küsten von Ländern rund um den Globus. Als ein Telefon, dass eine neue Generation von ZenFone Geräte von ASUS markiert, die ZenFone 2 stellt eine weitere Chance für ASUS in den Märkten Westeuropa und Nordamerika zu brechen.</p>\n<p>Obwohl die ZenFone 2 ist eine zweite Generation ZenFone, das Gerät ist es am ehesten gelingt es dem ZenFone 5. Die Benennung mag seltsam erscheinen, aber es ist aufgrund der ASUS weg von ihrer ursprünglichen Namensschema, wo die Zahl repräsentiert die Größe des Displays. Diese Art der Nennung ist nicht gut skalieren, wenn Sie Ihre Geräte jährlich aktualisieren müssen, so dass die 2 in ZenFone 2 bezeichnet es als eine zweite Generation ZenFone.</p>\n<p>Obwohl die ZenFone 2 beginnt bei nur $ 199, sollten Sie sich nicht vom Preis täuschen. Die ZenFone 2 hat einige sehr beeindruckende Spezifikationen für eine Low-Cost-Smartphone, startet mit einem ziemlich leistungsstarken Intel Quad-Core-Atom-SoC, 2 GB + RAM und eine 5,5 \"1080p-IPS-Bildschirm. Wir werden einen Blick auf jede seiner Komponenten in der Tiefe im Laufe der Überprüfung, Sie können jedoch einen Blick auf eine Übersicht über die ZenFone 2 specs unten zu nehmen.</p>\n<!--:--><!--:en--><p>When I think about ASUS, the first thing that comes to mind are their PC components like motherboards, GPUs and the like. I also think of their desktop and laptop computers. Part of that is probably due to my longstanding interest in PCs and PC gaming, but even so, the idea of ASUS as a smartphone company is one that I don\'t think about that often. However, ASUS has been offering smartphones since the days of Windows Mobile, and they\'ve been a very important player in the Android tablet space with their transformer tablets and both generations of the Nexus 7. With smartphone + tablet hybrids like the ASUS PadFone, it was seemingly inevitable that ASUS would become a competitor in the world of discrete Android smartphones.</p>\n<p>While ASUS has been making progress in the Asia-Pacific region, they haven\'t made as much progress in North American markets as I suspect they had hoped to. That brings us to today with the ZenFone 2. After initially going on sale in ASUS\'s home country of Taiwan on March 8th, and more recently in Japan and India, the ZenFone 2 has now made its way to the shores of countries around the globe. As a phone that marks a new generation of ZenFone devices from ASUS, the ZenFone 2 represents another chance for ASUS to break into the markets of Western Europe and North America.</p>\n<p>Although the ZenFone 2 is a second generation ZenFone, the device it most directly succeeds is the ZenFone 5. The naming may seem strange, but it\'s due to ASUS moving away from their original naming scheme where the number represented the size of the display. That type of naming doesn\'t scale well when you need to refresh your devices every year, and so the 2 in ZenFone 2 designates it as a second generation ZenFone.</p>\n<p>Although the ZenFone 2 starts at just $199, you shouldn\'t be deceived by the price. The ZenFone 2 has some extremely impressive specifications for a low-cost smartphone, launching with a fairly powerful Intel quad-core Atom SoC, 2GB+ of RAM, and a 5.5\" 1080p IPS screen. We\'ll be taking a look at each of its components in depth over the course of the review, but you can take a look at an overview of the ZenFone 2\'s specs below.</p>\n<!--:-->','The Asus Zenfone 2 Review','','inherit','closed','closed','','336-revision-v1','','','2015-09-15 12:35:14','2015-09-15 12:35:14','',336,'http://asus-zenpad.stagingapps.net/id/blog/2015/09/15/336-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(411,1,'2015-09-15 12:35:15','2015-09-15 12:35:15','<!--:en-->Rebooting your system\n\nHit the \"Pause/Break\" key when you see ASUS xxxx ACPI BIOS Revision\"\n\nFor example：A7N8X-VM represents the motherboard model\n2 Please find the model name from the motherboard surface\n\nIf necessary, please open the system case for better inspection.\n\nFor example：P4C800-E represents the motherboard model<!--:-->','How to Find Model Name','','inherit','closed','closed','','335-revision-v1','','','2015-09-15 12:35:15','2015-09-15 12:35:15','',335,'http://asus-zenpad.stagingapps.net/id/blog/2015/09/15/335-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(412,1,'2015-09-15 12:35:15','2015-09-15 12:35:15','<!--:en--><p>\n<p>The social roles theory suggests that social contexts have different gender role expectations and those gender role expectations can maximize or minimize gender differences. For instance, there are three competing hypotheses as to why and in what situations certain people hold <span class=\"GramE\">doors</span> for others. The gender neutral stance hypothesizes an equal amount of door holding would consistently be done by both sexes for both <span class=\"GramE\">sexes</span>. Chivalry is associated with male roles and is another hypothesis that predicts that men hold doors open for women as an act of helpfulness. Yet another stance looks at male dominance and how it is expressed in door holding behavior. This stance adds to the social role theory hypothesizing that door holding behaviors will be different depending on the emphasis on gender roles in the social context. The research done by Yoder, Hogue, Newman, Metz and LaVigne (2003) looks at door holding behavior in a dating situation as opposed to everyday life situations, predicting that males will hold open doors more often during a dating situation than in an everyday life situation. Seven hundred and sixty-nine mixed-gender, college-age, male-female pairs were unobtrusively observed in 16 different locations. The locations selected were places where either dating or non-dating couples were most likely to be found. These locations included shopping malls, universities and fast-good restaurants, for non-dating couples, and sit down restaurants and skate rinks, for dating couples. The amount of door holding for the other, either male of female, was measured. In an everyday context 55.2% more women, in the couples observed, held the door open for men than men did for women. In a dating context the reverse was found, 66.8% more men, in the couples <span class=\"GramE\">observed,</span> held the door open for women than women held the door open for men. This study contradicts studies done about 20 years ago, which suggests that door holding practices and gender roles have changed somewhat over the years in everyday life scenarios but remain similar in dating scenarios. Applying these results to the social role theory also suggests that door holding behavior may be different in dating versus everyday life scenarios because gender roles are more prominent in dating scenarios.</p>\n<p></p>\n<!--:-->','Exploring Moderators of Gender Differences','','inherit','closed','closed','','334-revision-v1','','','2015-09-15 12:35:15','2015-09-15 12:35:15','',334,'http://asus-zenpad.stagingapps.net/id/blog/2015/09/15/334-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
